    {
      "component": "article",
      "metadata": {
        "source": "github.readme"
      },
      "html": "\n<p>This is a sample project using the <a href=\"http://sass-guidelin.es/#architecture\">7-1 architecture pattern</a> and sticking to <a href=\"http://sass-guidelin.es\">Sass Guidelines</a> writing conventions.</p>\n<p>Each folder of this project has its own <code>README.md</code> file to explain the purpose and add extra information. Be sure to browse the repository to see how it works.</p>\n<h2>Using the indented syntax</h2>\n<p>This boilerplate does not provide a <code>.sass</code> version as it would be painful to maintain both versions without an appropriate build process. However, it is very easy to convert this boilerplate to Sass indented syntax.</p>\n<p>Clone it, head into the project and then run:</p>\n<pre>sass-<span class=\"hljs-built_in\">convert</span> -F sass -<span class=\"hljs-built_in\">T</span> scss -i -R ./ &amp;&amp; <span class=\"hljs-built_in\">find</span> . -iname <span class=\"hljs-string\">&quot;*.sass&quot;</span> -exec bash -c &apos;mv <span class=\"hljs-string\">&quot;$0&quot;</span> <span class=\"hljs-string\">&quot;${0%\\.sass}.scss&quot;</span>&apos; {} \\;</pre>"
    },
    {
